  <title class="- topic/title ">Redirector</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Use a Redirector similarly to how you
	 use an mbox in your tests. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <keyword>mbox</keyword>
      </keywords>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
    <p class="- topic/p ">Redirectors are created with a special Redirector URL
		that loads a Redirector mbox (Redirector) into your account. Use this
		Redirector similarly to how you use an mbox in your tests. Submit the
		Redirector URL to your Ad Network as the ad's destination link. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">Use the Redirector to 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">
      <ul id="ul_3EC65336B8814C4FB76B353BCF9B0880" class="- topic/ul ">
        <li id="li_5A54F0F7A1D64DD88469B1ED5BB7C909" class="- topic/li "> Track
		  clicks from your display ads to your site 
		</li>
        <li id="li_2FE2C6F8ABF7432E8DC634D79689AA2C" class="- topic/li "> Create
		  a single centralized report to track clicks to display ads on multiple ad
		  networks 
		</li>
        <li id="li_3638B12650094E0F93572077E97949EE" class="- topic/li "> Vary
		  display ad destinations 
		  <p class="- topic/p ">For example the same banner lands on your home
			 page, category page and product page. 
		  </p></li>
        <li id="li_F1C5D266606B4700ADB07F4EB302A603" class="- topic/li "> Find
		  which landing page leads to the most conversions 
		</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">For help deciding the right setup see 
		<xref href="c_Testing_Ads.xml#concept_C824F400EAA34B9489FF765F87FD6DBD" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref "><?xm-replace_text Using Behavioral Ads?></xref>.
		
	 </p>
  </conbody>
